    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p> <p><strong>Chop</strong> the pistachios coarsely</p> <p><strong>Peel</strong> and finely chop (or grate) the garlic</p> <p><strong>Combine</strong> the lamb mince, garlic, sultanas, cumin and pistachios in a mixing bowl</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-pistachio-meatballs/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Season</strong> the mixture generously with salt and pepper</p> <p><strong>Mix</strong> everything with clean hands</p> <p><strong>Divide</strong> and roll into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">(12)</span> even balls, then refrigerate until step 5</p> <p>Tip: Chilling the meat helps it hold its shape when cooking</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-pistachio-meatballs/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, cut the potatoes (with skins on) into bite-size chunks</p> <p><strong>Add</strong> the potatoes to a pot (with a matching lid) of salted boiling water</p> <p><strong>Boil</strong> on a high heat, covered, for 10-15 min or until you can pierce them easily with a fork</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-pistachio-meatballs/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, peel the carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span>, discarding the root end<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span></p> <p><strong>Continue</strong> to peel lengths off the carrot until you have a pile of carrot 'ribbons' and grate the remaining core&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Place</strong> the ribbons in a bowl of cold water &nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Chop</strong> the coriander finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-pistachio-meatballs/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Heat</strong> a wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tsp)</span> vegetable oil on a medium-high heat&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>When</strong> hot, add the meatballs and cook for 4 min or until browned&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Cover</strong>, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for a further 8-10 min&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Shake</strong> them about a bit for even cooking!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-pistachio-meatballs/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, combine the pomegranate molasses in a large mixing bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(4 tbsp)</span> olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper</p> <p><strong>This</strong> is your pomegranate dressing</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-pistachio-meatballs/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> the potatoes are tender, drain and return them to the cooking pot&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Add</strong> a knob of butter and a splash of milk and mash until smooth</p> <p><strong>Season</strong> generously with salt and pepper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lamb-pistachio-meatballs/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the carrot ribbons (drained) and coriander to the dressing bowl and mix well</p> <p><strong>Serve</strong> the meatballs over the mash with the carrot salad to the side</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
